Name: AirPollutionRating
Description: The vehicle's Air Pollution rating (1-10). refer http://www.greenvehicleguide.gov.au/

Name: ANCAPRating
Description: The ANCAP Safety Rating. Values from 1 to 5.

Name: Badge
Description: The Badge description of the vehicle Eg EXECUTIVE

Name: BodyConfiguration
Description: The Body Configuration description of the vehicle. Eg: DAY=Day Cab, DUAL=Dual Cab, HCUB=Hi Cube, NARW=Narrow Cab

Name: BodyStyle
Description: The Body Style description of the vehicle. Eg:BC=Bus Chassis,BDB=B-double,BUS=Bus,CAB=Cabriolet,CC=Cab

Name: CountryOrigin
Description: The Country of Origin description of the vehicle Eg Germany, Japan

Name: Cylinders
Description: Number of cylinders or rotors

Name: DoorNumber
Description: Number of doors not including the boot

Name: Drive
Description: The Drive description of the vehicle. Eg: 4X4, 4X4 Constant, 4X4 Dual Range, 4X4 On Demand, 6X2, 6X4, 6X6, 8X4, 8X8,

Name: EmissionStandard
Description: Which Emission standard this vehicle complies to. Eg: EU2=Euro 2, EU3=Euro 3, EU$=Euro 4, EU5=Euro 5

Name: EngineCode
Description: Manufacturer's engine code.

Name: EngineCycle
Description: The Engine Cycle description of the vehicle Eg 2 Stroke, 4 Stroke

Name: EngineDescription
Description: The common engine reference name, blank if there is no common name Eg 3.4

Name: EngineLocation
Description: The location of the engine. Eg: E=Mid-Rear, F=Front, M=Mid-Front, R=Rear

Name: EngineSize
Description: The engine capacity in cc's eg 3387

Name: EngineType
Description: The Engine Type description of the vehicle. Eg: E=Electric, P=Piston, PE=Piston - Electric, R=Rotary

Name: FuelCapacity
Description: The Fuel tank capacity in litres

Name: FuelCity
Description: The Urban fuel consumption measured in litres per 100km

Name: FuelCombined
Description: The Combined fuel consumption measured in litres per 100km

Name: FuelDelivery
Description: The Fuel Delivery description of the vehicle. Eg: C=Carburettor Single, CM=Carburettor Multiple,

Name: FuelHighway
Description: The Extra-Urban fuel consumption measured in litres per 100km

Name: FuelType
Description: The Fuel Type description of the vehicle.  Eg: A=Petrol or LPG (Dual), D=Diesel, E=Electric, G=LPG only, O=Petrol - Premium ULP, P=Petrol

Name: GearNumber
Description: The number of Gears on the vehicle

Name: GearType
Description: The Gear Type description of the vehicle. Eg; A=Automatic, AO=Automatic Overdrive, DS=Seq. Manual Auto-Dual Clutch, M=Manual

Name: GreenhouseRating
Description: The vehicle's Greenhouse rating (1-10) based on CO2 emissions. refer http://www.greenvehicleguide.gov.au/

Name: GrossCombinationMass
Description: The total of the gross weight and braked towing capacity (kg)

Name: GrossVehicleMass
Description: The maximum laden mass of a motor vehicle as specified by the Manufacturer (kg)

Name: Induction
Description: The Induction description of the vehicle Eg A=Aspirated, S=Supercharged, TSI=Turbo Supercharged Intercooled, TTI=Twin Turbo Intercooled

Name: KerbWeight
Description: The weight of the vehicle with standard equipment unoccupied and unladen with all fluid reservoirs full (kg)

Name: ModelCode
Description: Manufacturer's model code

Name: ModelYear
Description: The year in which the vehicle was manufacturered/assembled.

Name: OverallGreenStarRating
Description: The vehicle's overall rating (1-5) based on the sum of the air pollution and greenhouse ratings. refer http://www.greenvehicleguide.gov.au/

Name: RimMaterial
Description: The material of the rim. Eg: Alloy or Steel

Name: RonRating
Description: The recommended fuel RON rating

Name: Roofline
Description: Description of roof style, primarily for wagons and vans, ie: low roof, high roof

Name: SeatCapacity
Description: The number of occupants that can be legally carried

Name: Series
Description: The series of a vehicle model as specified by a manufacturer e.g. VY Commodore, FG Falcon

Name: Steering
Description: The Steering description of the vehicle Eg 4 Wheel Steering, Rack and Pinion

Name: TareMass
Description: The weight of the vehicle with standard equipment unoccupied and unladen with all fluid reservoirs full except for fuel, which is 10 litres only (kg)

Name: TowingBrakes
Description: Towing capacity - with brakes (kg)

Name: TowingNoBrakes
Description: Towing capacity - without brakes (kg)

Name: ValvesCylinder
Description: Number of valves per cylinder

Name: VehicleHeight
Description: Height of a vehicle at its highest point, measured from the ground with standard tyres fitted - typically meausured in millimetres.

Name: VehicleLength
Description: Length of a vehicle at its longest point, measured from bumper to bumper and typically referred to in millimetres.

Name: VehicleType
Description: Type of vehicle Eg PS-Passenger vehicle, LC-Light commercial, SV-SUV, HC-Heavy Commercial

Name: VehicleWidth
Description: Width of a vehicle measured at its widest point, typically referred to in millimetres.

Name: VFactsClass
Description: The VFacts Class

Name: VFactsPrice
Description: The VFacts Pricing Segment

Name: VFactsSegment
Description: The VFacts Segment

Name: VIN
Description: Sample of the Vehicle Identification Number.

Name: WarrantyKM
Description: The number of km the warranty covers (-1 = Unlimited)

Name: WarrantyYears
Description: The number of years on the car warranty

Name: Wheelbase
Description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels (mm)

Name: WheelbaseConfiguration
Description: The Wheel Base configuration of the vehicle, ie: LWB, SWB etc
